# IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF CLARK COUNTY
# STATE OF MAYFLOWER

Tomskipetski5,
Plaintiff,

v.

SheStoleMyXR,
Defendant.

Case No. CV 400-25

# DEFENDANTS RESPONSE TO COMPLAINT

Defendant SheStoleMyXR, by and through his counsel of record, orangebear22, hereby responds to the Complaint filed by Plaintiff Tomskipetski5 as follows:

GENERAL DENIAL

Pursuant to Rule [Insert Rule Number] of the Clark County Rules of Civil Procedure, Defendant denies each and every allegation contained in the Complaint, except those expressly admitted herein.

RESPONSES TO SPECIFIC ALLEGATIONS

Defendant admits the allegations in Paragraphs 12 regarding residency.

Defendant denies the allegations in Paragraphs 314 for lack of sufficient knowledge or because they are false, misleading, or omit material facts. Defendant specifically denies any unlawful or tortious conduct and asserts that any in-game events occurred within the bounds of lawful gameplay and server rules.

Defendant denies the allegations in Paragraphs 1517, except admits to engaging in conversation with Plaintiff, but denies that such conversation constitutes an admission of liability.

Defendant denies the allegations in Paragraphs 1822 and denies liability under 5 M. STAT. 3101.4.

Defendant denies the allegations in Paragraphs 2328 and denies liability under 5 M. STAT. 3103.2.

Defendant denies the allegations in Paragraphs 2934 and denies liability under 5 M. STAT. 3103.3.

AFFIRMATIVE DEFENSES

Without admitting liability, Defendant asserts the following affirmative defenses:

Failure to State a Claim The Complaint fails to allege facts sufficient to constitute a cause of action upon which relief can be granted.

Assumption of Risk Plaintiff voluntarily participated in activities within a simulated environment where the risk of in-game harm, loss, or death is inherent.

Consent Plaintiff implicitly consented to the risk of damage and loss by engaging in the game environment.

Mitigation of Damages Plaintiff failed to take reasonable steps to mitigate any alleged damages.

Lack of Jurisdiction over Subject Matter To the extent the claims are based solely on in-game interactions, the Court lacks jurisdiction.

De Minimis Harm The alleged damages are trivial in nature and not actionable.

PRAYER FOR RELIEF

WHEREFORE, Defendant respectfully requests that the Court:

a. Dismiss the Complaint in its entirety with prejudice;
b. Award Defendant costs of suit and reasonable attorneys fees; and
c. Grant such other relief as the Court deems just and proper.

DATED: August 14, 2025
Camp Bryant, Clark County

Respectfully submitted,

# orangebear22
Counsel of Record

Governor of the State of Mayflower
